    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p class="p--has-dropcap p-large-text" id="0h8xCh"&gt;While splashy chatbots may get all the attention, generative AI has real potential to &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/14/24177991/apple-intelligence-siri-voice-assistant-amazon-alexa-generative-ai"&gt;make the smart home simpler and more accessible&lt;/a&gt;. Amazon has already announced its &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/20/23880764/amazon-ai-alexa-generative-llm-smart-home"&gt;plans for a smarter Alexa&lt;/a&gt; to power your home. Now, it’s Google’s turn to promise that it can produce a better, smarter, more helpful Google Assistant. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="KKEwdh"&gt;Ahead of its fall hardware event next week, &lt;a href="https://blog.google/products/google-nest/gemini-google-home/"&gt;Google announced&lt;/a&gt; three new &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/24176860/google-gemini-explained-ai-assistant"&gt;Gemini intelligence-powered&lt;/a&gt; experiences it plans to bring to its &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/23744291/google-smart-home-nest-how-to"&gt;Google Home&lt;/a&gt; smart home platform later this year. There’s a new camera intelligence feature that generates descriptive captions for video footage from &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/22739349/google-nest-indoor-cam-wired-review-smart-security-camera"&gt;Nest cameras&lt;/a&gt;, a natural language input for creating &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/23428772/google-home-household-routines-how-to-set-up"&gt;Google Home routines&lt;/a&gt;, and a smarter Google Assistant for Nest smart speakers and displays...&lt;/p&gt;
